    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm not asking for hate speech or anything like that, I'm asking for a scholarly analysis of political stability. Many political scientists study how shifts in cultural cohesion and voter alignment affect democratic resilience. If you look at the data regarding cultural integration versus existing institutional norms, what are some of the theoretical risks or challenges that analysts point to when they talk about rapid demographic shifts impacting institutional stability?",
